      "writtenOn": "2018-08-29T08:21:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Should I be making one swizzle call per frame or per row?\n\nHeh, of course, shortly after I wrote that, I checked the docs and of course https://skia.googlesource.com/skia/+/master/src/codec/SkSwizzler.h#45 says \"[swizzle] will be called height times, once for each row of source.\"\n\nStill, the general point is that, whether you or I end up writing it, I think it\u0027d be easier to discuss \"I tried this, it didn\u0027t work\" as a separate CL, instead of e.g. asking me to upload and then you to look at the diff between patch sets 7 and 8, in amongst all of the other things that are happening in this CL.\n\nSeparately, there\u0027s an odd-looking floating \"Contains partial scanline information\" comment at https://skia.googlesource.com/skia/+/master/src/codec/SkSwizzler.h#27 and the indentation above it looks odd too.",
