      "writtenOn": "2018-09-15T03:51:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "FWIW, the Go stdlib\u0027s GIF decoder has been enforcing (literal_width \u003e\u003d 2) for 8 or 10 years now, and I don\u0027t remember anyone filing a bug about it. In constrast, I have seen lots of different Go GIF bugs, often along the lines of \"other GIF decoders accept such-and-such; why not Go?\", such as:\n\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/3565\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/5401\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/6441\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/8789\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/9856\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/10676\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/11150\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/20804\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/20856",
